LCHCmax3 Young - direct
BY MS. MENNINGER:
Q. And I think it's Jane, not Kate?
A. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
Q. That's fine. If you don't mind reading it again with Jane.
A. In the beginning, Jane would be with her mother and brothers at Epstein's house.
Q. Now, if I could have you take a look at the tab 3. Do you recognize this report?
A. Yes.
Q. This one actually was authored by your partner, Mr. Byrne or Detective Byrne; right?
A. Yes.
Q. But you checked his work?
A. Yes, I signed off on it.
Q. And this one relates to an interview that took place in November of 2019; right?
A. Yes, that's correct.
Q. And if I could direct your attention on this interview with Jane to the fourth full paragraph, the third line, begins Jane, Jane was not. If you could read that sentence with Jane.
A. Jane was not sure if Maxwell ever called her to make appointments.
Q. Thank you. And now if I could have you turn to tab 5. Are you there?
A. Yes.
SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
DOJ-OGR-00014179
